I can't speak for everyone of course, but 2017 was really a bounce back year for me after I had lost my grandma and 3 dogs the year prior and was still upset about all of them. So, when 2017 came around, I tried my best to be a better person in spite of respective loss and pain. This was a great year for me, and I feel like if YouTube were to start doing these again, everyone who saw them before would appreciate them for nostalgic reasons.
